 "2000-01-15T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow equitable relief where amendments or change orders to existing construction contracts are found void. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 5-18 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The provisions of this chapter, including \u00a7 5-18-19, do not abridge or alter rights of action or remedies in equity. 500 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 15451, "bill_version_id": 86235, "bill_version": "House State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2000-01-25T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow equitable relief if certain public contracts are found void. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 5-18-19 be amended to read as follows: 5-18-19. It shall be is unlawful for any public corporation or its officers to enter into any contract in violation of the terms of this chapter or chapter 5-21, and any such contract entered into shall be is null and void and of no force and effect. Nothing in this section prohibits the court from applying the doctrine of equitable estoppel. If the contractor affirmatively establishes grounds to apply the doctrine of equitable estoppel, the court may award the contractor some or all of the actual costs incurred in performing the contract. BILL HISTORY 1/15/00 First read in House and referred to State Affairs. H.J. 56 1/24/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 1/24/00 State Affairs Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 12, NAYS 1. H.J. 218"}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 15451, "action_date": "2000-01-15T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85628, "document_url